name: Action
description: Actions form a hierarchy. Application pages are generated from actions.

name: sectionStyle
description: Defines how to generate section children.

name: sectionColumns
description: Applicable to section style "Card". Defines how many columns shall be in a row of section cards.

name: inline
description: Inline action's content is displayed instead of an action link in navigation panels.

name: modalActivator
description: Inline action's content is displayed in a modal dialog which opens on a click on the action's link.

name: createLink
description: Creates a link pointing to this action and populated with action's text, icon, tooltip, and uuid attributes.

name: anonymous
description: Actions which are not shown in the containing action UI, but for which pages are generated and can be explicitly referenced, e.g. from content.

name: resources
description: Resources referenced by the page. Resource names are resolved relative to the page location.

name: rightNavigation
description: Right navigation panel.

name: navigation
description: Navigation items are displayed in the footer the root action, in the navigation bar for the principal action, and in the content panel navigation bar for the active action.

name: leftNavigation
description: Left navigation panel

name: sections
description: Actions which are generated into content sections. Id's of section actions are used to create URL fragments.

name: floatLeftNavigation
description: Float left navigation panel.

name: floatRightNavigation
description: Float right navigation panel.

name: ContentPanel
description: Content panel displays the primary page conent and can have a navigation bar and several navigation panels.

name: sectionColumns
description: Applicable to section style "Card". Defines how many columns shall be in a row of section cards.

name: sectionStyle
description: Defines how to generate section children.

name: breadcrumb
description: Breadcrumb items. Displayed on the top of the content panel.

name: title
description: Content title

name: sections
description: Content sections.

name: floatLeftNavigation
description: Navigation panel which float to the left of the content.

name: leftNavigation
description: Navigation panel to display on the left of the content.

name: floatRightNavigation
description: Navigation panel which floats to the right of the content.

name: rightNavigation
description: Navigation panel to display on the right of the content.

name: Footer
description: Footer is displayed below the navigation and content panels.

name: Header
description: Page header has a title on the left and a navigation bar on the right.

name: title
description: Header title displayed on the left.

name: Label
description: Label is a text and an icon with a tooltip, notification badge, and help dialog. Labels can have children. Label is a base class for Link.

name: notification
description: Notification to display next to the label. E.g. a number of new messages in an inbox.

name: tooltip
description: Label tooltip.

name: text
description: Label text.

name: id
description: Unique label ID, autogenerated by default.

name: outline
description: For some label representations specifies that the label shall be displayed as an outline instead of a solid fill.

name: icon
description: Label icon. Treated as URL if contains ``/`` or as a CSS class otherwise. E.g. ``fas fa-wrench`` would be treated as a CSS class.

name: children
description: Label children to build UI elements like trees, lists, navigation bars and drop-downs.

name: decorator
description: Decorator label or link. If present, is rendered next to the containing label. For example, a help icon with a tooltip, link, or modal.

name: script
description: Script to execute on link click (activation).

name: confirmation
description: Confirmation to display in a confirmation dialog before action activation to give the user an opportunity to cancel the action. E.g. confirmation of deletion.

name: target
description: Link target

name: name
description: Link name attribute if not blank for referencing sections.

name: location
description:
Link URL relative to the ancestor URL or ``base-uri``.

``${{{base-uri}}}`` token can be used in the activator to define the uri relative to the base generation URI (output folder) instead of the parent URI. 
It might be useful it the parent URI is an absolute external URI.
``${{{base-uri}}}`` ends with a slash, so there is no need to add a slash. E.g. ``${{{base-uri}}}index.html``.

name: action
description: Link to an action.

name: modal
description: Modal which opens on link activation.

name: NavigationBar
description: Navigation bar has a brand and navigation items.

name: brand
description: Brand label displayed on the left.

name: NavigationPanel
description: Navigation panel contains navigation items. Supports several styles.

name: id
description: ID for jsTree to store state between pages, e.g. expaned nodes.

name: style
description: Panel style

name: jsTreeSearchThreshold
description: Minimal number of tree nodes to show a search text input. Default is 0 - search is always shown.

name: Page
description: Application page consisting of several parts - header, navigation bar, navigation panel, content panel, and footer. Page extends Tag, but ``name`` attribute shall not be used - it defaults to ``div``.

name: navigationPanel
description: Navigation panel is positioned on the left of the content panel below the navigation bar.

name: header
description: Page header is displayed on the top of the page.

name: navigationBar
description: Navigation bar is displayed below the header.

name: contentPanel
description: Content panel is positioned on the right of the navigation panel below the navigation bar.

name: PagePart
description: Base class for page parts.

name: items
description: Navigation items.
